               <p>JOHN LEDWICK. I am a <rs id="t18241202-138-viclabel774" type="occupation">broker</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18241202-138-victim885 t18241202-138-viclabel774"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18241202-138-crimeloc775">High-street, Shadwell</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18241202-138-crimeloc775" type="placeName" value="High-street, Shadwell"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18241202-138-crimeloc775" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18241202-138-off772 t18241202-138-crimeloc775"></join>. On the 5th of November I received information from a little boy - I went into the street, and saw the prisoner, about four doors off, with my saw; he said, "What do you want with me, I was only going to play tricks with the boy; I did not mean to take the saw; here it is." It had hung against the middle post of my window.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18241202-138-person886">
                  THOMAS 
                  LEDWICK
               <interp inst="t18241202-138-person886" type="surname" value="LEDWICK"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18241202-138-person886" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18241202-138-person886" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . - I am ten years old. I am the prosecutor's son. I saw the prisoner take down the saw and walk away with it - he did not say any thing. I told my father, and we ran out. When he saw me, he said he was only playing tricks, to see what I should do.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18241202-138-person887">
                  WILLIAM 
                  SPOONER
